%% Interval data flow - StreamConsumer + IntervalReader (alternate trigger path)
%% Real-time events drive per-domain Redis sorted sets and SQS batch-start signals
%% IntervalReader coordinates per-domain inflight reading on a 15-min cron
%% Output goes to FIFO queue feeding aggregation - DynamoDB - IntervalAggregator
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant ACD as ACD or DFO
    participant KO as Kinesis<br/>Orch Stream
    participant STC as StreamConsumer<br/>Java
    participant Q as SQS IR Queue<br/>prefixed AC, CS,<br/>ACDFO, CSDFO, AS
    participant R as Redis sorted sets<br/>ac, cs, acdfo, csdfo, as<br/>:inflight
    participant LST as IntervalReader<br/>SQSQueueListener<br/>JMS
    participant SCH as IntervalReader<br/>Scheduler cron
    participant IRS as IntervalReaderService
    participant FIFO as SQS NICEWFM_IR_SA_QUEUE<br/>.fifo
    participant EXT as SQS external<br/>batch-completion queue
    participant IA as IntervalAggregator<br/>downstream

    ACD->>KO: interval-relevant orchestration event
    KO->>STC: KCL read

    Note over STC: For each event domain
    STC->>R: ZADD score timestamp to domain sorted set
    STC->>Q: SQS notify with prefix e.g. AC underscore timestamp

    Note over LST,SCH: IntervalReader process model
    Q->>LST: JmsListener receives batch-start signal
    LST->>LST: store batch-start timestamp in system property

    Note over SCH: Cron tick every 15 minutes
    SCH->>IRS: process batchStartTs
    IRS->>R: ZRANGEBYSCORE per domain
    R-->>IRS: inflight refs
    IRS->>FIFO: SendMessage per-tenant MessageGroupId
    SCH->>EXT: NotifyExternalApplication

    Note over FIFO,IA: Downstream aggregation eventually writes DynamoDB. IntervalAggregator then reads DynamoDB to produce S3 files. See diagram 02.
    FIFO-->>IA: consumed by aggregation path
